  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at AIG?",
  "response": "Starting a new job can be both exciting and overwhelming. Here are some key things new employees should know when starting their first day at AIG (American International Group):\n\n1. **Company Culture**: AIG emphasizes a culture of integrity, teamwork, and innovation. Understanding and embodying these values can help new employees integrate more smoothly.\n\n2. **Onboarding Process**: Familiarize yourself with the onboarding schedule and any training sessions you will be attending. This process is designed to help you acclimate to the company.\n\n3. **Dress Code**: AIG generally follows a business professional dress code, but it may vary by department. It\u2019s a good idea to check with your manager or HR if you\u2019re uncertain.\n\n4. **Meet Your Team**: Take the time to introduce yourself to your colleagues. Building relationships early on can help you feel more comfortable and supported.\n\n5. **Understand Your Role**: Make sure you are clear about your job responsibilities, expectations, and how your role fits into the broader company objectives.\n\n6. **IT and Tools**: Familiarize yourself with the technology and tools you\u2019ll be using, such as software applications, communication platforms, and any other systems relevant to your position.\n\n7. **Company Policies**: Review the employee handbook or any materials provided about company policies, including those related to conduct, diversity and inclusion, and benefits.\n\n8. **Resources and Support**: Know where to find resources, such as HR contacts, IT support, and your manager. Having this information can help you troubleshoot any issues quickly.\n\n9. **Feedback Mechanisms**: Be aware of how feedback is given and received at AIG. Understanding the review process and how to ask for feedback can help you grow within the company.\n\n10. **Networking Opportunities**: Look for opportunities to connect with other employees, whether through formal networking events or informal gatherings. Building a network can be beneficial for your career growth.\n\n11. **Learning and Development**: AIG often encourages continuous learning. Explore any available training programs, mentorship opportunities, or professional development resources.\n\n12. **Health and Safety**: Familiarize yourself with any health and safety protocols, especially if you are working on-site. This may include emergency procedures and workplace ergonomics.\n\n13. **Work-Life Balance**: Understand the company's stance on work-life balance and any policies regarding remote work or flexible hours.\n\n14. **Company News and Updates**: Stay informed about company news, announcements, and updates. This can help you feel more connected and engaged with the organization.\n\n15. **Ask Questions**: Don\u2019t hesitate to ask questions if you\u2019re unsure about something. It\u2019s better to seek clarification than to make assumptions.\n\nBy keeping these points in mind, new employees can set themselves up for success and make the most of their first day at AIG.",
